The 2018 MyBroadband Cyber Security Conference took place on 22 August 2018 at The Venue in Melrose Arch, and was hosted in partnership with Vodacom. This exclusive technical conference focused on cybersecurity threats and provided insight into how companies and individuals could protect against these threats. The event featured top cybersecurity experts as speakers, including Vodacom Chief Technology Security Officer Darshan Lakha and SensePost CTO Dominic White. Topics at the conference included Wi-Fi security, defence versus offence, security problems with Internet of Things devices, and attack simulation in an EDR world. Delegates also had the opportunity to solve a security challenge. 180 delegates started the challenge, and 25 delegates were able to solve all the problems. Here is a look at the 2018 MyBroadband Cyber Security Conference.                         